        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 18 at 1:48PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 148 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Cokedale, or near Trinidad, moving east at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trinidad, Cokedale, Starkville, Gulnare, Raton Pass, Boncarbo,
Segundo, and Hoehne.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
